comment._content: EKA-3B Skywarrior Bu No 142650 seen in this overexposed 'bled' 'flickr' offering by SDASM Archives. VAQ-129 Modex 615. Tail code NP of CVW-21 USS Hancock Note ECM aerial 'teardrop' shapes on fuselage before and behind wing. Possible time period may be deduced from here: www.gonavy.jp/CVW-NPf.html Some time before or between Oct.22, 1970 & June 2, 1971 (Vietnam War deployment) And here to confirm that VAQ-129 was equipped with KA-3B, one of which was 142650 Modex 615. www.gonavy.jp/CVW21-NP1970.html The above aircraft may also be viewed in these two SDASM 'flickr' pics: www.flickr.com/photos/sdasmarchives/4564060459/ www.flickr.com/photos/sdasmarchives/4564691140/ Thanks to San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive for all pictures of EKA-3B 142650.
